with%2055-year-old%20Alice%20Peacock%20from%20Reading%2C%20England.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20fully%20intended%20to%20go%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-went-back-to-work-4-weeks-after-giving-birth-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eback%20to%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20having%20my%20first%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20looked%20into%20nurseries%20near%20my%20workplace%20and%20tried%20to%20get%20increased%20flexibility%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-i-organize-5-hour-workday-entrepreneur-small-business-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecut%20my%20hours%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20my%20company%2C%20but%20nothing%20seemed%20to%20be%20working%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20first%20child%2C%20Michael%2C%20was%20born%20in%202001%2C%20and%20I%20fell%20in%20love.%20When%20my%20maternity%20leave%20was%20coming%20to%20an%20end%2C%20I%20questioned%20whether%20I%20wanted%20someone%20else%20to%20look%20after%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20decided%20to%20give%20my%20one-month%20notice%20and%20take%20a%20break.%20Motherhood%20kept%20me%20busy%2C%20and%20I%20had%20my%20second%20child%2C%20Melissa%2C%20in%202005.%20I%20didn't%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-full-time-job-after-staying-home-kids-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereturn%20to%20a%20full-time%20job%3C%2Fa%3E%20until%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%2017%20years%20away%20from%20corporate%20made%20me%20a%20softer%20and%20kinder%20person.%20When%20I%20began%20looking%20for%20full-time%20jobs%20again%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freturning-to-work-from-a-career-break-what-i-learned-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecareer%20returners%20program%3C%2Fa%3E%20helped%20me%20get%20back%20into%20the%20corporate%20world.%20I'm%20now%20working%20at%20the%20same%20level%20as%20I%20was%20when%20I%20left%20IT.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b105660f-b6d1-425d-a463-a3c3df2e1467%5C%22%3ELeaving%20my%20job%20to%20look%20after%20the%20kids%20was%20like%20a%20permanent%20holiday%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20really%20enjoyed%20being%20part%20of%20the%20corporate%20world.%20I'd%20been%20working%20in%20operations%20for%20an%20IT%20services%20company%20since%201998.%20I%20understood%20my%20work%20and%20felt%20good%20at%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20hard%20to%20leave%20my%20job%20in%202001.%20I'd%20built%20up%20a%20reputation%20and%20felt%20connected%20to%20my%20colleagues.%20I%20invited%20the%20whole%20global%20team%20to%20my%20wedding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20looking%20after%20the%20children%20was%20like%20a%20permanent%20holiday.%20When%20you've%20got%20time%20to%20spend%20with%20your%20kids%2C%20you%20can%20instill%20lessons%20into%20them%20so%20they%20can%20be%20independent.%20My%20children%20can%20cook%2C%20and%20they%20know%20the%20value%20of%20money.%20I'd%20always%20make%20sure%20they%20finished%20a%20meal%20when%20we%20went%20out%20to%20eat%2C%20and%20not%20be%20wasteful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20back%20of%20my%20mind%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20go%20back%20to%20work%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20think%20I%20could%20handle%20a%20corporate%20operations%20job%20alongside%20the%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2249342c76-1e27-43cb-ae2a-f8b992cf43a9%5C%22%3EWhile%20I%20wasn't%20working%2C%20we%20relied%20on%20my%20partner's%20income%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsave-money-quickly-tips-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecut%20back%20on%20expenses%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20having%20shorter%20holidays%20and%20not%20sending%20our%20kids%20to%20private%20school%2C%20but%20we%20were%20willing%20to%20make%20these%20sacrifices%20so%20I%20could%20stay%20home%20and%20look%20after%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20my%20children%20were%20growing%20up%2C%20I%20did%20take%20on%20some%20part-time%20work%20and%20voluntary%20opportunities.%20My%20money%20wasn't%20required%20to%20contribute%20to%20the%20household%20resources%2C%20but%20I%20missed%20adult%20conversation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2299b9ef54-be7f-43c4-816c-e774d446a64d%5C%22%3EI%20considered%20going%20back%20to%20full-time%20work%20because%20of%20a%20comment%20my%20son%20made%20sometime%20in%202017%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%2016-year-old%20son%20got%20a%20job%20at%20a%20grocery%20store%20back%20in%202017%2C%20he%20made%20a%20cheeky%20joke%20that%20he%20was%20making%20more%20money%20than%20I%20did.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20eldest%20was%20a%20teenager%2C%20and%20my%20daughter%20was%20old%20enough%20to%20go%20to%20school%20by%20herself%2C%20so%20I%20started%20looking%20for%20operations%20jobs%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20knew%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fresume-gap-how-to-explain-why-job-search-career-linkedin-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emy%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20gap%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20be%20a%20barrier%2C%20so%20I%20was%20open%20to%20lower-level%20roles%20than%20I%20had%20when%20I%20left%20IT.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20attended%20employment%20workshops%20at%20a%20local%20community%20center%2C%20where%20we%20learned%20about%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%2C%20LinkedIn%2C%20and%20interview%20techniques.%20Actively%20preparing%20for%20employment%20made%20me%20feel%20confident%20about%20the%20job%20search.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20hiring%20manager%20I%20spoke%20to%20told%20me%20they%20were%20looking%20for%20someone%20with%20more%20recent%20experience.%20Not%20long%20after%20that%2C%20I%20was%20accepted%20into%20a%20three-month%20employment%20program%20I%20heard%20about%20and%20applied%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2204a8c0b4-1ab2-4987-8537-5ec7441e98e8%5C%22%3EGetting%20into%20a%20career%20returner's%20program%20helped%20me%20transition%20back%20into%20full-time%20work%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20program%20was%20with%20O2%2C%20a%20British%20telecommunications%20company%20now%20known%20as%20Virgin%20Media%20O2.%20The%20program%20was%20designed%20specifically%20for%20people%20returning%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-six-figure-tech-job-gap-year-gen-z-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecareer%20breaks%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20like%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20coincidental%20that%20the%20program%20was%20accepting%20applicants%20at%20the%20same%20time%20I%20started%20job%20searching.%20Without%20this%20kind%20of%20specialized%20scheme%2C%20it%20would've%20been%20a%20bigger%20challenge%20to%20get%20back%20into%20work%20because%20I%20lacked%20recent%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20program's%20interviewers%20considered%20my%20transferable%20skills%20and%20asked%20me%20how%20things%20I%20did%20during%20my%20career%20break%20might%20apply%20to%20the%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20the%20program%20in%20October%202018%20and%20settled%20easily.%20It%20felt%20like%20I'd%20never%20left%20the%20workforce.%20I%20received%20support%20from%20my%20line%20manager%2C%20a%20mentor%2C%20and%20my%20peers%20in%20the%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20three%20months%2C%20I%20was%20offered%20a%20full-time%20position%20as%20a%20problem%20process%20manager.%20The%20role%20overlaps%20with%20my%20previous%20experience%2C%20and%20I've%20found%20the%20operations%20processes%20similar%20to%20when%20I%20was%20last%20in%20the%20workforce.%20Technology%20has%20changed%2C%20though%2C%20because%20now%20we%20have%20things%20like%20Teams%20for%20video%20calls%2C%20and%20there's%20more%20virtual%20collaboration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c09c35ba-c015-465e-85ae-c49186fc6eae%5C%22%3EMy%20career%20break%20has%20made%20me%20softer%20and%20kinder%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20promoted%20to%20senior%20problem%20manager%20in%202022.%20I'm%20probably%20on%20the%20same%20level%20now%20as%20I%20was%20before%20having%20kids.%20However%2C%20had%20I%20not%20stopped%20working%20in%202001%2C%20I%20think%20I%