ecided%20to%20try%20nesting%20after%20their%20marriage%20ended.%3Cp%3ETara%20Moore%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EWhen%20my%20ex%20and%20I%20divorced%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20try%20%26quot%3Bnesting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOur%20kids%20stay%20in%20the%20family%20home%2C%20and%20we%20alternate%20parenting%20them%20there%20and%20staying%20in%20an%20apartment.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20helps%20us%20coparent%20better%2C%20keeps%20things%20stable%20for%20the%20kids%2C%20and%20is%20financially%20responsible.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdetermined-marriage-end-in-divorce-backfired-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emarriage%20ended%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20more%20than%20two%20decades%2C%20I%20wasn't%20ready%20to%20uproot%20everything%20all%20at%20once.%20We%20had%20two%20kids%2C%20a%20shared%20house%2C%20and%20years%20of%20routines.%20So%20instead%20of%20rushing%20to%20sell%20or%20move%20out%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20try%20something%20I'd%20only%20heard%20about%20in%20passing%3A%20%26quot%3Bnesting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbird-nesting-divorce-parenting-plan-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENesting%20means%20keeping%20the%20family%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20the%20primary%20base%20for%20our%20kids%20while%20my%20ex%20and%20I%20alternate%20living%20there%20and%20staying%20elsewhere.%20We%20change%20places%20halfway%20through%20the%20week%2C%20and%20the%20kids%20never%20have%20to%20pack%20a%20bag.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b9620b61-37a6-43de-a4d0-c5f8fcbfb3c3%5C%22%3EThere%20are%20some%20perks%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20options%20we%20discussed%2C%20nesting%20not%20only%20sounded%20good%20for%20the%20kids%20but%20was%20also%20the%20most%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbird-nesting-divorce-minimize-chaos-for-kids-kept-routine-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinancially%20responsible%20option%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20live%20in%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20where%20rents%20are%20sky%20high%2C%20and%20having%20two%20homes%20large%20enough%20to%20support%20the%20kids%20isn't%20really%20a%20possibility%20right%20now.%20After%20alternating%20on%20friends'%20couches%20for%20a%20while%2C%20we%20rented%20a%20studio%20apartment%20as%20our%20second%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20ex%20and%20I%20alternate%20spending%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbird-nesting-divorce-success-guide-tips-rules-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehalf%20the%20week%20parenting%20in%20the%20family%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20other%20half%20in%20a%20sleek%2C%20modern%20studio%20with%20building%20amenities%20like%20a%20gym%20and%20a%20hot%20tub.%20The%20apartment%20is%20clean%2C%20quiet%2C%20and%20honestly%2C%20kind%20of%20incredible.%20There%20are%20no%20toys%20on%20the%20floor%2C%20no%20dog%20hair%2C%20and%20no%20scooters%20in%20the%20hallway.%20Sometimes%20I%20just%20sit%20quietly%20on%20the%20couch%20to%20hear%20myself%20think.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENesting%20can%20feel%20surreal.%20The%20house%20stays%20the%20same%2C%20but%20we%20rotate%20in%20and%20out%20like%20actors%20in%20a%20long-running%20play.%20One%20night%2C%20I'll%20be%20folding%20laundry%20and%20helping%20with%20homework%2C%20and%20the%20next%2C%20I'll%20be%20alone%20in%20the%20studio%20apartment%20eating%20cereal%20for%20dinner.%20There%20is%20some%20whiplash%2C%20as%20my%20environment%20changes%20every%20couple%20of%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222d2b75d5-7466-42fd-a7ee-bcc1e6821582%5C%22%3ECooperation%20and%20communication%20are%20essential%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbird-nesting-divorce-pros-cons-for-kids-parents-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehardest%20part%20of%20nesting%3C%2Fa%3E%20isn't%20emotional.%20It's%20logistical.%20There%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20sharing%20and%20coordinating.%20We%20lay%20out%20a%20schedule%20in%20a%20combined%20calendar.%20We%20share%20grocery%20lists%20and%20update%20each%20other%20on%20the%20house%20and%20kid%20status%20when%20we%20switch%20places.%20We%20agreed%20not%20to%20leave%20either%20house%20messy%2C%20to%20let%20each%20other%20know%20our%20comings%20and%20goings%2C%20and%20to%20change%20the%20sheets%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20if%20someone%20brings%20a%20date%20home%2C%20which%20is%20a%20whole%20other%20world%20to%20navigate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20moments%20when%20communication%20breaks%20down%2C%20when%20we%20snap%20at%20each%20other%2C%20or%20when%20resentment%20starts%20creeping%20in.%20Sometimes%2C%20the%20towels%20are%20in%20a%20new%20place.%20Sometimes%2C%20my%20ex%20forgets%20to%20take%20the%20trash%20out.%20Sometimes%2C%20I%20leave%20my%20socks%20on%20the%20floor.%20This%20arrangement%20takes%20a%20level%20of%20cooperation%20that%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fno-fault-divorce-after-one-year-marriage-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edivorced%20couples%3C%2Fa%3E%20might%20not%20be%20willing%20to%20do.%20We're%20not%20just%20co-parenting%3B%20we're%20cohabiting%20without%20coexisting.%20My%20ex%20is%20my%20roommate.%20In%20two%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22102055df-5dbc-4e9b-a1d6-313dae46ca73%5C%22%3EIt's%20not%20forever%2C%20but%20it's%20buying%20us%20time%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENesting%20isn't%20a%20permanent%20solution%2C%20and%20we%20both%20know%20that.%20The%20kids%20will%20get%20older%20and%20our%20lives%20will%20evolve%2C%20so%20we're%20figuring%20out%20how%20long%20this%20arrangement%20can%20last.%20In%20the%20short%20term%2C%20it%20gives%20us%20space%20to%20keep%20stability%20in%20the%20kids'%20lives.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20don't%20have%20to%20switch%20houses%20or%20bounce%20between%20bedrooms.%20Their%20lives%20stay%20constant%2C%20even%20as%20ours%20shift.%20They%20roll%20with%20the%20alternating%20parents%20and%20try%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20ever-changing%20schedule%20of%20who's%20home.%20I%20think%20they%20appreciate%20having%20access%20to%20both%20of%20us%20and%20treasure%20having%20their%20own%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20moments%20I%20miss%20having%20my%20own%20uninterrupted%20home%2C%20and%20get%20sick%20of%20packing%20a%20bag%20every%20few%20days.%20But%20when%20I%20think%20of%20my%20kids%20having%20to%20move%20back%20and%20forth%20after%20their%20parents%20split%20up%2C%20I%20know%20I'd%20rather%20do%20it%20for%20them.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnesting-divorce-helps-coparent-financially-responsible-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1749547261000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6846f2d1f748d8c055f34a91%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnesting-divorce-helps-coparent-financially-responsible-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22My%20ex%20and%20I%20are%20'nesting'%20after%20our%20divorce.%20Our%20kids%20stay%20in%20the%20family%20home%2C%20and%20we%20alternate%20time%20there%20and%20in%20an%20apartment.%20It%20helps%20us%20coparent.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Lauren%20Palmigiano)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnesting-divorce-helps-coparent-financially-responsible-2025-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Housefull%205'%20box%20office%20collection%20day%205%20(LIVE)%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1749547258000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-121750193%2Cimgsize-49988.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fbox-office%2Fhousefull-5-box-office-collection-day-5-live-the-akshay-kumar-film-expected-to-remai